CodeLists.term: Males and postmenopausal females at least 50 years of age.

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: Diagnosis of probable AD as defined by NINCDS and the ADRDA guidelines.

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: Modified Hachinski Ischemic Scale score of <= 4.

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: CNS imaging (CT scan or MRI of brain) compatible with AD within past 1 year. (See Protocol for incompatible findings.)

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: Investigator has obtained informed consent signed by the patient (and/or legal representative) and by the caregiver.

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: Geographic proximity to investigator's site that allows adequate follow-up.

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: Caregiver will monitor administration of prescribed medications, and will be responsible for the overall care of the patient at home.

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: Use of any investigational agent or approved Alzheimer's therapeutic medication within 30 days prior to enrollment into the study.

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: Serious illness which required hospitalization within 3 months of screening.

CodeLists.name: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
CodeLists.term: Diagnosis of serious neurological conditions (See Protocol)

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive AEENTPT
Methods.description: If AEENRTPT is populated, AEENTPT is DM.RFPENDTC for the subject.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive CMENTPT
Methods.description: If CMENRTPT is populated, CMENTPT is DM.RFPENDTC for the subject.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive DAYCALC
Methods.description: Study day relative to RFSTDTC. Date - RFSTDTC + 1 if on or after RFSTDTC. Date - RFSTDTC if date precedes RFSTDTC.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive DISEQ
Methods.description: Starts at "1" for first device identifier and increments by one for each DIPARM

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive DTHFL
Methods.description: If DTHDTC is populated then DTHFL='Y'

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive EPOCH
Methods.description: EPOCH from SE where date >= SESTDTC and date < SEENDTC

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive EXDOSE
Methods.description: EXDOSE = ECDOSE * ECPSTRG expressed in mg.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive FTSTRESN
Methods.description: If FTSTRESC is numeric then FTSTRESN=FTSTRESC in numeric format, else null.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive IEORRES
Methods.description: If IECAT=INCLUSION then IEORRES=N, else if IECAT=EXCLUSION then IEORRES=Y

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive LBSTRESC
Methods.description: LBSTRESC is equal to LBORRES or the value in standard units if a conversion is necessary.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive LOBXFL
Methods.description: Set to "Y" for last record with non-null original result on or before the first dose date (RFXSTDTC). Null otherwise.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive QSSTRESC_PH
Methods.description: If QSORRES="Not at all" then 0 If QSORRES="Several days" then 1 If QSORRES="More than half the days" then 2 If QSORRES="Nearly every day" then 3

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive QSSTRESC_PH_10_11
Methods.description: QSSTRESC=QSORRES

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive QSSTRESC_SL
Methods.description: If QSORRES="Strongly disagree" then 1 If QSORRES="Disagree" then 2 If QSORRES="Slightly disagree" then 3 If QSORRES="Neither agree nor disagree" then 4 If QSORRES="Slightly agree" then 5 If QSORRES="Agree" then 6 If QSORRES="Strongly agree" then 7

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive QSSTRESN
Methods.description: If QSSTRESC is numeric then QSSTRESN=QSSTRESC in numeric format, else null.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive RFENDTC
Methods.description: The Date of Study Completion or Early Termination. Null for screen failures.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive RFPENDTC
Methods.description: The latest date of assessment for the subject as determined by the End of Study Form, any scheduled assessments, Adverse Events, or Concomitant Medications.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive RFSTDTC
Methods.description: The first date/time of study drug. Null for screen failures.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive RFXENDTC
Methods.description: The last date/time of study drug administration. Null for subjects with no treatment data.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive RFXSTDTC
Methods.description: The first date/time of study drug administration. Null for subjects with no treatment data.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive RSSTRESC
Methods.description: RSSTRESC is the corresponding numeric value of RSORRES according the values shown on the HAMD-17 CRF page.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive SEENDTC
Methods.description: SEENDTC is set to the start of the next Element, or RFPENDTC for the last Element.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive SEQ
Methods.description: Unique sequence number within a subject, restarting at 1 for every subject, applied to sorted data.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive SESTDTC
Methods.description: SESTDTC if set to the --DTC for that subject which exists in the data for the defined start of the Element, such as DSSTDTC when DSDECOD=INFORMED CONSENT OBTAINED for Screening Elements or min(EXSTDTC) for Dosing Elements.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive STRESN
Methods.description: If --STRESC represents a numeric value then --STRESN is the numeric version of --STRESC, else null. "--" represents the domain code.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive SVENDTC
Methods.description: For each scheduled visit, SVENDTC = the last (max) date associated with a subject for that visit. For unplanned visits, SVENDTC is the date of the visit.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive SVSTDTC
Methods.description: For each scheduled visit, SVSTDTC = the first (min) date associated with a subject for that visit. For unplanned visits, SVSTDTC is the date of the visit.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive TSSEQ
Methods.description: Unique sequence number within each TSPARM, restarting at 1 for per TSPARM, applied to sorted data.

Methods.name: Algorithm to derive VSSTRESC
Methods.description: Data collected in conventional units (i.e. F, lbs, inches) is converted using standard conversion factors to standard units (C, kg, cm).
